    dc:title "An extraordinary new fluvial bdelloid rotifer, Coronistomus impossibilis gen. nov. sp. nov., with adaptations for turbulent flow (Rotifera: Bdelloidea: Coronistomidae fam. nov.)" ;
    fabio:hasPart <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4736214>, <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4736216>, <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4736212>, <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4736218>, <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4736222>, <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4736224>, <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4736226>, <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4736228>, <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4736230>, <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4736232>, <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4736234> ;
    a fabio:JournalArticle .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4736214>
    dc:description "FIGURE 2: Coronistomus impossibilis gen. nov., sp. nov., composite drawing of feeding animal from the ventral side based on photographs. Only selected features of the internal anatomy are shown." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/4736214/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4736216>
    dc:description "FIGURE 3: Coronistomus impossibilis gen. nov., sp. nov., preserved holotype with open corona-mouth (shrunken to ~65% of live size). A, dorsal aspect. B, ventral aspect. Each image is a stack of three photographs. ca: caudal appendage; cn: corona; rm: rostrum; vmg: ventromedial gland." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/4736216/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4736212>
    dc:description "FIGURE 1: Most of the specimens of Coronistomus impossibilis gen. nov., sp. nov. were from the submerged surfaces of the rock facing the current in the foreground (arrow), Hawlings River, 30 May 2019." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/4736212/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4736218>
    dc:description "FIGURE 4: Coronistomus impossibilis gen. nov., sp. nov., live specimen with corona withdrawn, slightly compressed.A, entire animal crawling. B, details of anterior body. ca: caudal appendage; lp: lappet; vmg: ventromedial gland." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/4736218/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4736222>
    dc:description "FIGURE 5: Coronistomus impossibilis gen. nov., sp. nov., eyespots and other details of live specimens.A, holotype, lateral. B, paratype, dorsal. es: eyespot; lf: longitudinal fold; lp: lappet; pp: papillae." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/4736222/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4736224>
    dc:description "FIGURE 6: Coronistomus impossibilis gen. nov., sp. nov., preserved holotype. A-E, focus series of open corona-mouth moving from ventral side towards dorsal side. F, diagrammatic representation of primary features of head.All to the same scale. cn: corona; ll: lower lip; mt: mouth; rm: rostrum; sr: semicircular ridge; ul: upper lip." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/4736224/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4736226>
    dc:description "FIGURE 7: Coronistomus impossibilis gen. nov., sp. nov. compared with Adineta beysunae Örstan. A, live specimen showing the circular rim of integument surrounding the corona-mouth. B, same specimen preserved. C, A. beysunae, slightly compressed live specimen.All to the same scale. cr: circular rim; re: ring-muscle; rm: rostrum." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/4736226/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4736228>
    dc:description "FIGURE 8: Bdelloid trophi compared. A, Coronistomus impossibilis gen. nov., sp. nov. B, Philodina sp. C, Abrochtha sp. ipt: interproximal teeth." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/4736228/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4736230>
    dc:description "FIGURE 9: Coronistomus impossibilis gen. nov., sp. nov. A, preserved specimen (stained with neutral red), dorsal aspect. B, egg of the holotype with attached debris (stack of four photographs; brightfield). C, live specimen, lateral aspect of posterior body. All to the same scale. as: anal swelling; ca: caudal appendage; dtg: dorsotransverse gland; vm: vitellarium." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/4736230/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4736232>
    dc:description "FIGURE 10: Coronistomus impossibilis gen. nov., sp. nov., details of foot anatomy.A, preserved compressed specimen, foot. B, live specimen, toes. C, live specimen, caudal appendage with two pairs of ducts (a, a’, b, b’) and a pair of muscles (c, c’). D, live specimen, foot. an: attachment nib; ca: caudal appendage; dlc: dorsolateral gland complex; vmc: ventromedial gland complex." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/4736232/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4736234>
    dc:description "FIGURE 11: Coronistomus impossibilis gen. nov., sp. nov., caudal appendage used as a pivot during crawling.A, body and and caudal appendage aligned. B, body turned 90° with respect to caudal appendage. ca: caudal appendage; rm: rostrum." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/4736234/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

